    {
      "id": "be2db76a_ecb10ec8",
      "file_path": "packages/docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 8,
      "message": "Not sure about the \"upgrade\", haven't seen much of it before in Docker images.\n\nIn any case, I think mariadb-client is a package that should be in \"policy-common-alpine\" or \"policy-base-alpine\" for all images.   All of them use mariadb, and I think it would be beneficial to include the client in all of them.\n\nI just put together some thoughts about structuring the software in your ticket INT-995.   I think it would be benefitial to have all this base software snapshotted in an official release, so applications would be immune of any changes underneath in a development release.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
